  <heading>LUTI6 (16-bit)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Lookup table read with 6-bit indices (16-bit)</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction copies indexed 16-bit elements from the low 512 bits of
the two table vectors to the destination vector using packed 6-bit indices
from a segment in the bottom three quarters of the source vector register.</para>
      <para>This instruction is unpredicated.</para>
      <para>This instruction requires that the Effective SVE vector length is at least
512 bits.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>False</predicated>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
    <operationalnote>
      <operationalnote_content>
        <para>This instruction is a data-independent-time instruction as described in <xref linkend="ARMARM_BEICCDDAB3">About PSTATE.DIT</xref>.</para>
      </operationalnote_content>
    </operationalnote>
  </operationalnotes>
